'''金橘''' is the Chinese name for [[kumquat]].  In Mandarin Chinese it is pronounced ''jīnjú'' (literally "golden orange"), and it is pronounced ''gam1 gwat1'' in Cantonese.  An alternate name preferred by Cantonese speakers is [[柑橘]], also pronounced ''gam1 gwat1'' in Cantonese (gān jú in Mandarin, literally "large tangerine orange").

